# GNOME Shell Extension Guard Rails

## CRITICAL -- Async Only
All `Gio.Subprocess` calls MUST use `communicate_utf8_async()`. Synchronous subprocess
or file I/O in extension context freezes the entire GNOME Shell. Pattern:

```javascript
const proc = Gio.Subprocess.new(argv, Gio.SubprocessFlags.STDOUT_PIPE | Gio.SubprocessFlags.STDERR_PIPE);
const [stdout, stderr] = await proc.communicate_utf8_async(null, null);
```

## CRITICAL -- Error Containment
Every async call MUST be wrapped in `try/catch`. Unhandled exceptions propagate to
`gnome-shell` and crash it. On Wayland, recovery = logout/login.

## St Widgets Only
Extensions cannot use Gtk widgets. Use: `St.BoxLayout`, `St.Label`, `St.Icon`,
`St.ScrollView`, `St.Button`. No `Gtk.` imports.

## FileMonitor Debounce
`Gio.FileMonitor` fires twice during atomic writes (tmp create + rename).
Debounce with `GLib.timeout_add(200, ...)` before refreshing the UI.

## Shell Version
`metadata.json` must include all supported versions: `["45","46","47","48","49"]`.
Test on the host version (GNOME 49.4).

## Cleanup in disable()
All `GLib.timeout_add` handles, `Gio.FileMonitor` instances, and `Gio.Subprocess`
references MUST be cleaned up in `disable()`. GNOME calls `disable()` on screen lock,
extension toggle, and shell restart. Leaked resources crash the shell.

## Logging
Use `console.log()` / `console.error()` (GNOME 45+ API). Prefix all messages
with `[cursor-schedule]`. Output goes to `journalctl -f /usr/bin/gnome-shell`.
